The coordinates of the vertices of the polygon are given as: 1. \((0, 1 - \sqrt{3})\) 2. \((1, 1 - \sqrt{3})\) 3. \((3 - \sqrt{3}, \sqrt{3} - 2)\) 4. \((\sqrt{3}, 0)\) 5. \((\sqrt{3}, 1)\) 6. \((3 - \sqrt{3}, 3 - \sqrt{3})\) 7. \((1, \sqrt{3})\) 8. \((0, \sqrt{3})\) 9. \((\sqrt{3} - 2, 3 - \sqrt{3})\) 10. \((1 - \sqrt{3}, 1)\) 11. \((1 - \sqrt{3}, 0)\) 12. \((\sqrt{3} - 2, \sqrt{3} - 2)\) 13. \((0, 1 - \sqrt{3})\) Using the shoelace formula, we calculate the area by summing the products of the coordinates and taking the absolute value of half the result. The area is then: \[ \text{Area} = \frac{1}{2} \left| -46 + 32\sqrt{3} \right| = 16\sqrt{3} - 23 \] This area can be written in the form \(m\sqrt{n} + p\) where \(m = 16\), \(n = 3\), and \(p = -23\).
